The paper deals with game theory and equilibrium concepts, which are typically studied in the cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design) sub-category. The use of algorithms and optimization techniques to find equilibrium concepts suggests a connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the predictive power of the proposed equilibrium concepts, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the consideration of punishment in the cooperative equilibrium concept suggests a connection to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category, which often deals with the study of social behavior and incentives.
